Package ohos.utils

Class IntArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.utils.IntArray

  • public class IntArray
extends Object
    A collection class of int arrays. This class encapsulates commonly used operations on IntArray for you to invoke. It also supports basic operations regarding generic stacks, so that you can use them as int stacks.

    When the int primitive data type is stored into a generic collection class, it is automatically converted into a corresponding data type. This process is known as autoboxing, which however, will deteriorate performance to some extent. To resolve this issue, this class is used to store the int primitive data as a collection class, without the autoboxing process. This class supports automatic scaling of arrays so that you do not need to worry about the array capacity.

    Pay attention to the following when using the IntArray class: This class is non-thread safe and is not recommended for service concurrency.

    Since:
    1

      • binarySearchInInsArray

        public int binarySearchInInsArray​(int value)
        Searches for a specified value using the binary search algorithm. If no result is found, a negative value is returned. However, you can invert this negative value to obtain the index where the value should be inserted into the current IntArray object.

        Note that the binary search must be performed on ordered arrays. Therefore, before calling this method, you must use the sortIns() method to sort values in the object. Otherwise, the returned result is uncertain.

        Parameters:
        value - Indicates the value to search for.
        Returns:
        Returns the index of the value; returns a negative value if no result is found.
